## Nest a Fetch Inside a Case Dispatch Over a Recall

Recall a user preference. Use `case` to select which resource to fetch based on the preference.

```scheme
(case (cortex/recall :topic \"theme\")
  ((dark) (fetch \"https://api.assets.local/css/dark.css\"))
  ((light) (fetch \"https://api.assets.local/css/light.css\"))
  (else (fetch \"https://api.assets.local/css/default.css\")))
```

The recall returns a symbol like `'dark`. The `case` matches the branch. The corresponding fetch fires. One form. One recall. One wire hop. The case closes the consequent fetch; the fetch closes the form.

---

## Nest a Fetch Inside a Map Over a Let-Bound Filtered List

Fetch a list of product IDs. Filter for IDs > 1000. Bind the filtered list in a `let`. Map over the list to fetch details for each ID. Return the list of product names.

```scheme
(let ((ids (filter (lambda (n) (> n 1000))
                   (json-parse (fetch \"https://api.catalog.local/product-ids\")))))
  (map (lambda (id)
         (json-ref (fetch (string-append \"https://api.catalog.local/product?id=\" (number->string id)))
                   \"name\"))
       ids))
```

The innermost fetch returns a JSON array of IDs. `json-parse` converts it to a list. `filter` keeps IDs > 1000. The `let` binds the filtered list. `map` fires a detail fetch for each ID and extracts the name. One `let` form. One initial fetch. N detail fetches. The map closes the body; the body closes the `let`.

---

## Nest a Fold Over a Fetched List with a Knowledge Lookup Per Item

Fetch a list of animal names. For each animal, look up its average lifespan (from knowledge, assume it returns a number). Sum the lifespans.

```scheme
(fold (lambda (animal acc)
        (+ acc (knowledge/of :category \"lifespan\" :subject animal)))
      0
      (json-parse (fetch \"https://api.nature.local/animals\")))
```

The fetch returns a JSON array of animal names. `json-parse` converts it to a list. `fold` iterates, performing a knowledge lookup for each animal (returning a number) and adding it to the accumulator. One form. One wire hop. N knowledge lookups. The fold closes the sum; the sum closes the form.

*[needs: `knowledge/of` returning a numeric value when category is a quantifiable attribute]*  
<!-- BUILD: knowledge/of should coerce numeric strings to numbers when category semantics indicate quantity -->

